manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: The dinosaur is coming，Come explore together！ Your child can build three different color of dinosaurs, including Tyrannosaurus Rex, Triceratops, and Velociraptor. Use our electric drill and hand drill to assemble the dinosaurs. Explore the dinosaur world together and spend hours of entertainment. The wonderful gift for boys girls age 3-7 year old. As a birthday gifts, Halloween gifts, Christmas gifts, give a big surprise to your little kids.

More Details Two-Way Electric Drill The electric drill has two types of drill bits that can be replaced at will and can be rotated in both directions to tighten or loosen screws. Attention: Need 2*AA batteries, NOT INCLUDED Hand Drill Equipped with a hand drill suitable for children's small hands, it is easy to operate and can exercise children's hands-on ability. Smooth Edge The three dinosaurs are designed with obtuse angles, and the edges are smooth without hurting your children hands.
Movable Parts Mouth can be opened at any time Twist up and down the cute limbs Make different poses flexibly

Diverse assembly brings different surprises! Children can use their imagination and creativity, combine dinosaur parts at random to form a special dino. Random assembly can break the inherent thinking, improve children's thinking and hands-on ability and develop comprehensively. Stem toys for 3 4 5 6 7 year olds is a great gifts，promote the healthy growth of children.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very fun, not as easy as it looks.
reviews.reviewText: The toy is very fun. You completely construct the dinosaurs yourself. I bought a set each for my twin 4yo thinking they would love it. They do, however it's too difficult for them to do by themselves. The pieces have to be held together at the correct, and sometimes difficult, angle to get the plastic screws in. This is a great toy for young ones who like to tinker and also want or need a bit of a challenge.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Such a great gift for kids who love taking things apart and putting them together again! This was definitely the favorite gift

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
Reviewed in the United States on May 10, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Build yourself a dinosaur
reviews.reviewText: Edit: The kid has played with this a lot. One of the dinos is missing an arm and there's several screws now missing. I have removed the screw bit. Fun toys but the screws come loose as they're played with. Keep the screwdriver handy. Really not the perfect gift for a three year old who learned how to reverse the driver... I ordered this for a three year old enamoured of dinosaurs. He was completely smitten with the box and just couldn't wait until Papa could help build. Probably few three year old kids could make the dinos by themselves. But the kid was engrossed in the process and used the battery operated screwdriver to set each screw. Papa helped to get the screws started. The dinosaurs are sturdy and the little boy has played with them a lot. I hid the screwdriver. Without papa's help, I don't think I can put them back together...

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fun way for a child to learn some power tool and assembly skills
reviews.reviewText: I got these as a present for my four year old daughter. She caught on to doing it quickly and has assembled and disassembled them several times now. You can see her skill and confidence building each time.

reviews.reviewText: Gifted this toy for the holidays to my best friend's 2 year old, who is obsessed with it. But two of the three dinosaurs were missing limbs, while there were duplicated parts of the remaining dinosaur. Whoever sorted the pieces into boxes did a poor job.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 8, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So much fun!
reviews.reviewText: I bought this for my son's 5th birthday and all of us loved it.We all day together and built them. It took time, trial and error, figuring out how to do it. It wasn't that difficult, it was the perfect thought provoking toy and at the end my son felt good about himself because he built a really cool dinosaur.Definitely recommend! Love the price as well.

reviews.reviewTitle: Le han encantado a mi ahijado
reviews.reviewText: Contentísimo estaba, pese a ser un poco más pequeño de la edad recomendada. Le ha dado mucha satisfacción montarlo, desmontarlo, probar combinaciones... Un juguete divertido.

Design dei dinosauri sfizioso, giocabilità eccellente, bambini dai 2 ai 4 anni che ci si sono divertiti moltissimo, ovviamente aiutati nel montaggio. Una volta montato solido ma anche con gli arti che si muovono. Il miglior regalo qualità prezzo del 2021

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on February 18, 2021
reviews.reviewText: I loved the idea of this product as my 3 year old grandson is obsessed with dinosaurs. We made the first 2 together, I lined up the screws while he used the drill to secure the parts. It was great fun. The downside is when it came to assembling the TRex, there were several parts missing including the head so it has no eyes and it looks like a crocodile. I think it would be value for money if all the parts were there and now looking at other reviews this was a problem for a few too. I haven't been able to see how to contact the seller to replace this one Dino without sending it all back.
